<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using elimination.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}+{7}{y}=-{56}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{7}{x}-{9}{y}=-{31}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({7},-{2}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to use the first equation to eliminate x from the second equation.</p>
<p>To eliminate we need the scaled version of equation one to have a coefficient of --7. So we scale by <m>\displaystyle--\frac{{7}}{{-{{6}}}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{-{7}}}{{-{{6}}}}{\left(-{6}{x}+{7}{y}\right)}=-\frac{{-{7}}}{{-{{6}}}}{\left(-{56}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{\left(-{7}\right)}{x}+-{8.1666666666667}{y}={65.333333333333}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{7}{x}-{9}{y}=-{31}</m></p>
<p>Adding these two equations gives us</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{17.166666666667}{y}={34.333333333333}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{34.333333333333}}{{-{{17.166666666667}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{2}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}+{7}{\left(-{2}\right)}=-{56}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}+{\left(-{14}\right)}=-{56}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}=-{56}-{\left(-{14}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}=-{42}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{42}}{{-{{6}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={7}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({7},-{2}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

